[[File:Asa Lift 6 row top lifter carrot harvester.jpg|thumb|This is the 6 row Self Propelled carrot harvester Asa Lift started up in 2011]] [[File:SIMON carrot harvesters.jpg|thumb|A top lift and a share lift self-propelled carrot harvester manufactured by SIMON]] A '''carrot harvester''' is an agricultural machine for [[harvest|harvesting]] [[carrot]]s. Carrot harvesters are either top lifters or share lifters and may be [[tractor]] mounted, trailed behind a tractor or self-propelled.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.simon-online.fr/index.htm|title=Simon - Welcome|accessdate=8 October 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.asa-lift.com|title=Asa Lift Vegetable Harvesting Machines|accessdate=2012-12-04}}</ref> The machine typically harvests between one and six rows of carrots at once.
==Operation== The two types of harvesters differ in how they get the carrots from the ground.
===Top lifting harvesters=== Top lifters use [[Natural rubber|rubber]] belts to grab the green tops of the carrot plant and pull them from the [[soil]]. A share pushes under the carrot root and loosens the plant.
The belt takes the carrots, with tops, in to the machine where the tops are cut off and sent along a waste path and dropped back on to the field.
===Share lifting harvesters=== A share lifter uses a share to get the carrots out of the ground from underneath. The machine must be preceded by a topper to cut the green tops off the carrot plants. The carrots travel along a longer web to separate out the soil.
===Cleaning and collection=== The carrot roots travel along one or more webs to remove most of the soil attached to the carrot. The carrots are collected either in a storage tank on the machine or in a trailer pulled alongside the machine by another tractor.
